b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Canva AI is best suited for social media graphics, presentations, marketing materials, non designers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Hotpot AI, meanwhile, shines for quick edits, background removal, art generation, mockups, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2013, Canva AI describes itself as \"AI-powered design platform for creating marketing visuals.\" Hotpot AI, established in 2020, positions itself as \"AI tools suite for image generation, editing, and design.\" With 7 years between them, Canva AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Hotpot AI offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Canva AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 5.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Hotpot AI is a poor choice — far from it. Hotpot AI excels in its own right, particularly for quick edits and background removal.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value ai integrated into full design platform, go with Canva AI. If many useful ai tools in one place matters more to you, Hotpot AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
